[32;1m[1;3mThe patch to be backported changes the method `indexValue` in `ArrayIndexer.java` by adding the call to `noArrayLengthField()` on `docBuilder.noStoredField()` to avoid indexing array lengths for object arrays within object arrays.

From the code snippet of the older version (ref 140164b93ac4273f65f10a92ef555b6cbce8b2a8) that I viewed, the method `indexValue` currently looks like this:

```java
@Override
public void indexValue(@NotNull List<T> values, IndexDocumentBuilder docBuilder) throws IOException {
    docBuilder.translogWriter().startArray();
    for (T value : values) {
        if (value == null) {
            docBuilder.translogWriter().writeNull();
        } else {
            innerIndexer.indexValue(value, docBuilder);
        }
    }
    if (docBuilder.getTableVersionCreated().onOrAfter(Version.V_5_9_0)) {
        // map '[]' to '_array_length_ = 0'
        // map '[null]' to '_array_length_ = 1'
        // 'null' is not mapped; can utilize 'FieldExistsQuery' for 'IS NULL' filtering
        docBuilder.addField(new IntField(arrayLengthFieldName, values.size(), Field.Store.NO));
    }
    docBuilder.translogWriter().endArray();
}
```

The patch in the newer version changes this to:

```java
@Override
public void indexValue(@NotNull List<T> values, IndexDocumentBuilder docBuilder) throws IOException {
    docBuilder.translogWriter().startArray();
    var nestedDocBuilder = docBuilder.noStoredField().noArrayLengthField();
    for (T value : values) {
        if (value == null) {
            docBuilder.translogWriter().writeNull();
        } else {
            innerIndexer.indexValue(value, nestedDocBuilder);
        }
    }
    docBuilder.translogWriter().endArray();
}
```

The key difference is the introduction of `nestedDocBuilder` initialized as `docBuilder.noStoredField().noArrayLengthField()`, and passing this `nestedDocBuilder` to `innerIndexer.indexValue` instead of the original `docBuilder`. Also, the older version has logic to add the array length field conditionally, which is removed in the newer patch.

I also checked that `noArrayLengthField()` does not exist in the older version, so likely this method was introduced after the older ref.

Hence, to backport this, I need to consider:

- The older version does not have `noArrayLengthField()`, so I cannot call it.
- The older version calls `docBuilder.addField(new IntField(arrayLengthFieldName, values.size(), Field.Store.NO));` conditionally, which is removed in the newer patch.
- The newer patch removes the array length field addition, so I should remove it in the backport as well.
- The newer patch uses `nestedDocBuilder` to avoid adding array length fields in nested arrays.

Given this, to backport the patch, I can:

- Introduce a `nestedDocBuilder` initialized as `docBuilder.noStoredField()`.
- But since `noArrayLengthField()` does not exist, I cannot chain it.
- Pass `nestedDocBuilder` to `innerIndexer.indexValue`.
- Remove the conditional addition of array length field from the older code.

This will replicate the behavior of the newer patch as closely as possible in the older codebase.

I will now draft the patch accordingly.[0m

